<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-05-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-05-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="150" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d150">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Uhl</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Dun</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-05-18"><hi rend="italic">May 18,
                                1895</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>British Government informs the Department that the sealing regulations
                            for 1895 are not agreed to. Instruct consuls in Japan to refuse
                            privilege to British vessels in future under articles 4, 5, and 6, and
                            that regulations are still in force as to American vessels.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Uhl</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Acting.</hi></signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>